dct_title_s: Ethnographical Italo-Jugoslav-German frontier  / by Ant. Lazić.
dct_description_sm: Text is  filed in the Rodman Wanamaker Collection, 1894-1925. The pamphlets from this collection  are primarily from the period 1914-1921 bound together under call number: RECAP DR10 .J357, volume 3, printed number 1193 in upper right. Relief shown by shading. Shows The Old Austro Hungarian frontier ; Eastern boundary of the Italian claims according to the Treaty of London; Eastern boundary of the territory occupied by the Italian troops. Also underlines places of Jugoslav origin. Administrative boundaries Shows color coded locations of ethnic Jugoslavs (Serbs, Croats, and Slovenes);Jugoslavs included in the Italian electoral districts of Istria; Italians, and Germans.
